The paper proposes a deep convolutional network for visual attribute localization and ranking, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions that the network jointly learns the attribute's features, localization, and ranker, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions that the proposed method is faster than previous methods, which involves optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions that the proposed method achieves state-of-the-art results on various relative attribute datasets, which involves performance evaluation. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely sub-categories.
